friends = Array["Agnes", "Agatha", "Germaine", "Jack"]

puts friends[0]
*grabs first string*

puts friends[-1]
*access the array elements from the back of the array*

puts friends [0,2]
*grabs the first 2 elements in an array*

friends[0] = "Stacy"
*changes the first element at index position 0*

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

friends = Array.new 
*tells ruby that we want to make an array, but we don't want to put any values into it yet* 
friends[0] = "Jane" 
*puts "Jane" as index [0]

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

friends = Array["Agnes", "Agatha", "Germaine", "Jack"]
puts friends.length()
*how many elements are inside the array*

puts friends.include? "Agatha"
*checks to see what elements are inside of the array, gives true/false value if the element is in the array*

puts friends.reverse()
*will reverse all the elements*

puts friends.sort()
*sorts the array alphabetically*

P.S. Arrays can't have multiple data types 
